# Step 1: Create a plaintext file
echo "Hello mere bhai." > text.txt

# Step 2: Encrypt the file (AES example)
openssl enc -aes-256-cbc -pbkdf2 -in text.txt -out encrypted_msg.txt

# Step 3: Decrypt the file back
openssl enc -aes-256-cbc -pbkdf2 -d -in encrypted_msg.txt -out decrypted_msg.txt

# Step 4: Compare plaintext and decrypted file using diff
diff text.txt decrypted_msg.txt

# Step 5: Generate MD5 hash of plaintext
openssl md5 text.txt

# Step 6: Generate SHA256 hash of plaintext
sha256sum text.txt

# Step 7: Generate SHA256 hash of decrypted file
sha256sum decrypted_msg.txt

# Step 8: Compare hashes to confirm integrity
# If both hashes match, the files are identical

============================================

This file covers Topic 5: Hashing and Fingerprints — using diff, md5, and sha256sum to check file integrity and confirm that encryption/decryption preserved the original content.
